OSGSA R Workshop

Please register here: https://forms.gle/kFkLSNb6MjQtEhwb8 by November 1.

Seminar Description

If you know the basics in R but want to learn more about wrapping your code into functions, making reproducible workflows, and best practices, this is the workshop for you. We will talk about the process of building a large code project, strategies for debugging and troubleshooting, and resources to keep learning R on your own. This workshop is designed for people who have used R a few times for a class or project but want to build their skills and feel less frustrated. If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to hearno@mun.ca . Looking forward to seeing you there!

Question? Reach out to hearno@mun.ca or osgsa@mun.ca.
